# part 3: SSH
Generate SSH key and connect to different VM without password.

su - user3                    		 # Switch to user3 on the System VM
ssh-keygen -t rsa -b 4096    		 # Generate a new SSH key pair for passwordless login
ssh-copy-id ldap@ipaserver.example.com   # Copy the public key to the remote VM
ssh ldap@ipaserver.example.com           # Test passwordless SSH login

notes:
( Secure Shell ) It is a secure way to connect to another Linux server remotely.
This creates two keys:
id_rsa → your private key (keep this secret)
id_rsa.pub → your public key (can be shared)
Key length: 4096 bits (very strong).


